<subSubSection id="87269A4F297A82060F60A558E4C07282" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="comments">
<paragraph id="75B4A21EFABB81F6D27931555B906075" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E7CE71B6DAE1CD9A9C858EFD38C6B537" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Because 
<taxonomicName id="2AEFEAA8A8E6E163CFF8D9EAC0DD3AE5" class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia rhois" order="Pucciniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="rhois">Hemileia rhois</taxonomicName>
is based on urediniospores, 
<bibRefCitation id="2A3429930E0FDA7403CE35E8929A5E4E" author="Ritschel, A" journalOrPublisher="Bibliotheca Mycologica" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 132" title="Monograph of the genus Hemileia (Uredinales)." volume="200" year="2005">Ritschel (2005)</bibRefCitation>
published a new name for this species based on a type specimen with teliospores. With the new ICN, the correct name based on the rules of priority is the oldest one.
</paragraph>
